==English==

{{rfd}}
====Etymology====
A combination of the [[indefinite article]] "[[a]]" and "[[lot]]" 

===Adverb===
'''alot'''
# very [[many]]
#:''They have '''alot''' of things in their bag.''
# very [[much]]
#:''Thanks '''alot''' for helping me out.''
# [[often]]
#:''Yes, he does that '''alot'''.''

===Usage===
In all senses, a '''non-standard''' spelling of ‘a [[lot]],’ frequent in informal writing.